These verses mark a split between the second and third
scenes of the canto, the neutrals and those other sinners, of all
kinds, who are destined to begin their travel to their final
destinations in Charon's bark.  From this point on the action of the
canto moves to the near bank of Acheron.  The next canto will begin on
the other side of the river.
